wikipedia_page.main: Sir Eric Edward Bullus (20 November 1906 – 31 August 2001) was a British Conservative politician.  He was Member of Parliament (MP) for Wembley North from 1950 until the constituency was abolished by boundary changes for the February 1974 general election.
